cyclone.name: FRED
cyclone.current_location: about 65 mi SSW of Great Inagua Island
cyclone.trajectory: Tracking west-northwest across the southeastern Bahamas today, then turning northwest toward the Florida Keys on Saturday and the northeast Gulf Coast late Sunday.
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: Florida Panhandle/Alabama coast (near the FL-AL border)

weather_observation.watch_coast: Northern coast of Haiti, southeastern Bahamas, and several eastern-central Cuban provinces
weather_observation.warning_coast: None in effect (only watches issued as of Advisory #11)
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Southeastern Bahamas, northern Cuba, Florida Keys & South Florida, Florida west coast, and the north-central Gulf Coast (FL Panhandle to Alabama)
weather_observation.rainfall: Only remnant-related showers possible mid-next week; heavy rainfall is not expected to reach 4 inches.
